# ============================================================================
# Invoice Manager - Environment Variables
# ============================================================================
# 
# This file contains environment variables for the frontend application.
# 
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (or .env.local for local development)
# 2. Fill in your actual values below
# 3. The .env file is gitignored and won't be committed to the repository
#
# PRODUCTION:
# For production deployments, set these as environment variables on your
# hosting platform (e.g., Vercel, Netlify, Coolify, etc.)
# ============================================================================

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Supabase Configuration (Required)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Supabase Project URL
# Get this from your Supabase project dashboard: Project Settings > API
# Format: https://xxxxxxxxxxxxx.supabase.co
# For local development with Supabase CLI: http://127.0.0.1:54321
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321

# Supabase Anonymous Key (Public)
# Get this from your Supabase project dashboard: Project Settings > API
# This is the "anon" or "public" key (safe to expose in frontend code)
# Format: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local Development Notes
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# When running Supabase locally with `supabase start`, use:
# - VITE_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# - VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<get from `supabase status` output>
#
# To get your local anon key, run:
#   supabase status
# Look for "anon key" in the output

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Production Notes
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# - Never commit your .env file with actual credentials
# - Use your hosting platform's environment variable system for production
# - The VITE_ prefix makes these variables available in the browser
# - These are public variables (safe to expose in client-side code)

# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Additional Configuration
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Edge Functions have their own environment variables.
# See: supabase/functions/send-invoice-email/.env.local.example
